On April 14, 2009, Vice President Biden hosted two conference calls with governors and local officials to discuss the implementation of the Recovery Act. The purpose of the calls was to provide updates and gather input on how the act was being implemented across the country. Elected officials from various states and cities participated in the calls, including Governors Mitch Daniels, Jim Douglas, Jack Dalrymple, John Otter, and Deval Patrick, as well as Mayors Karl Dean, Darwin Hindman, Mary Hooper, R.T. Rybak, John Robert Smith, County Executive Barbara Fiala, and County Supervisor Linda Langston.